## Module extensions

- `*.py,*.wsgi,*.js,*.jsx,*.ts,*.tsx,*.css,*.pcss,*.styl,*.md,*.json,*.yml,*.yaml,*.sh`

```shell
pip install virtualenv virtualenvwrapper-win
# Machine global:
mkvirtualenv flask-sample-site-1903
workon flask-sample-site-1903
# Project local:
virtualenv .venv
call .venv/Scripts/activate
# Install all requirements:
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install flask
pip install Django==1.11.18
pip freeze django
pip freeze > requirements.txt
django-admin --version
python manage.py startapp testapp
```

Set variables:
```shell
WORKON_HOME=C:/Home/User/Envs
PYTHON_PATH=...
PATH=%PATH%;%PYTHON_PATH%;%PYTHON_PATH%/Scripts
VIRTUAL_ENV=.venv
```

NOTE: vim and python must be both 32 or 64 bit (32 bit on 2019.02.04 -- use 32bit Python27 -- python-2.7.15-32bit.msi)

